The paper deals with a fundamental problem in computational geometry of finding a path between two points that does not cross more than a certain number of obstacles. This problem is closely related to graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and provides algorithms for solving it, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of topological results and FPT algorithms, which are related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
